subSubSection.paragraph:
Enicospilus merdarius

– auctt., misidentification (e.g., 
Gauld & Mitchell 1981
; 
Horstmann 1997
).

Despite the coincidence of the species name, Haller’s specimens were not reared but were caught in the daytime, basking on vegetation (
Haller 1885
). There are no obvious habitat preferences discernible from the collection data.
